    <h2 id="-project-of-the-day-team-access-simulation">ğŸ›  Project of the Day: â€œTeam Access Simulationâ€</h2>
    <p><strong>Scenario:</strong><br />
A new <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">devops</code> team is being onboarded. Youâ€™ve been asked to configure user access and a shared directory.
<strong>Steps:</strong></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Create users: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">alice</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bob</code>, and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">guest</code></li>
      <li>Create group: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">devops</code></li>
      <li>Add <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">alice</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bob</code> to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">devops</code> group</li>
      <li>Create <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/opt/devops-data/</code> with group read/write</li>
      <li>Prevent <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">guest</code> from accessing <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/opt/devops-data/</code></li>
      <li>Log all permissions and test actions for each user
<strong>Deliverables:</strong></li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>Markdown: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">project-devops-access.md</code></li>
  <li>Screenshot: Group membership, permissions, access denied
